<br>
My Primaries are a 60 Ranger, 60 Cleric and 60 Warrior. I have a 51 Shaman also Im playing around with... as well as a 57 Warrior (retired him-gave to friend) and 52 Warrior (gave him to a friend) and a 48 Warrior.<br>
<br>
Its not hard playing 3. I dungeon crawl, play in ToV-NToV and many other places triple sessioning. I have not found a situation yet I cannot triple session in....<br>
<br>
Heres a GREAT hotkey to make and I recommend it :)<br>
<br>
Key name: FOLLOW<br>
Box #1: /target (main characters name)<br>
Box #2: /follow<br>
<br>
That will target your primary mover characters and then begin auto-following him/her.<br>
<br>
Beyond that hotkey I have no special setup other then an 'Assist' hotkey of my Ranger. Ranger is my main primary character who pulls and picks targets. My Warrior assists me in all cases.<br>
<br>
A lot of people ask me &quot;HOW do you do it!?! Your hands must be tired!&quot;<br>
<br>
Well guys, its not as hard as it looks.... if you have troubles just playing 1 characters then I certainly dont recommend 2+ at the same time :)<br>
<br>
